# CURSOR PRO TOOL ROUTING

Tell Ryan which tool to use when the task fits. Never make him guess.

## Tool Guide

### Debug with AI (Most Important for Ryan)
**When:** A red error appears in the terminal, or the app crashes or freezes.
**How:** Look for the "Debug" button that appears next to the red error text in the terminal panel. Click it. Cursor sends me the full error with context automatically.
**Do NOT** copy/paste the error manually — use the button. It gives me more information.

### @Codebase (Librarian Search)
**When:** Ryan asks "where is X?" or "how does Y work?" across multiple files.
**How:** In the chat box, type @Codebase before the question.
**Best model for this:** Switch to Gemini Flash in the model picker for near-instant results.
**Example:** `@Codebase where is the star counter used?`

### Notepads (@-Mentions for Reusable Context)
**When:** A chunk of information needs to be reused across many sessions.
**How to find in Cursor UI:**
Look in the LEFT SIDEBAR of Cursor for a small notebook/page icon. It may also appear as a tab in the chat panel. If you do not see it, your Cursor version may put it under a different label — check cursor.com/docs for "Notepads" in your version.

**If you cannot find Notepads at all:**
This project already achieves the same result through PROJECT_CONTEXT.md and PATCH_NOTES.md. These are always read at the start of sessions and serve the same purpose. You do not need Notepads for this project to work — they are a nice-to-have, not a requirement.

**If you do find and create Notepads, suggested ones:**
- `@Libby-Progress` — which stickers she has mastered (update as she levels up)
- `@Sprint-Goals` — current Phase 1 completion checklist

### Background Agents
**When:** A task is large and would take many minutes (e.g., "rebuild the entire mastery store and rewire QuestGrid").
**How:** In the chat, say "run this as a background agent." Cursor works while you do other things. Check back when notified.
**Caution:** Review all changes before accepting — background agents move fast.

### Review Changes (Before Any Commit)
**When:** Before committing code to git, especially before any session involving Libby testing the app.
**How:** Open Source Control panel (Ctrl+Shift+G) → click "Review with AI" on the diff.
**Goal:** Catch any visible bugs, developer-only text, or TinyStories violations before Libby sees the app.

### Cursor Tab (Always On)
**What it is:** AI autocomplete that appears as you type. Gray ghost text = Tab to accept.
**No action needed** — it is always running.

## Quick Reference Card

| Problem | Tool to use |
|---|---|
| Red error in terminal | Debug with AI button |
| "Where is X in the code?" | @Codebase + Gemini Flash |
| Reuse project context | @Notepad |
| Big multi-file task | Background Agent |
| Before committing | Review Changes |
| Writing new code | Cursor Tab + this chat |
